  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg1178">msg1178 (view)</a></th>
   <th>Author: jesstess</th>
   <th>Date: 2011-02-26.19:20:51</th>
   <th>
    
   </th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>The attached patch series adds a checkbox to each portfolio entry that lets you toggle whether or 
not you want to receive "maintainer updates" for this project. I envision maintainer updates 
meaning both maintainer update e-mails, and having the project in your managing-getting-in-
touch-with-new-contributors box, when that gets implemented.

What this patch series doesn't do is adjust the content of weekly e-mails. The reason is that this 
shift towards customizing the site experience for maintainers and new contributors means we 
should probably have distinct e-mails, or at least 2 different sections of the weekly e-mail: a 
maintainer updates section and a new contributor section (you currently get weekly e-mails for all 
projects in your portfolio and for which you've clicked the 'I want to help' button).

I think that level of change is outside the scope of this ticket. (Related issues include 1) the 
frequency of "weekly e-mails", <a href="issue284">issue284</a>, and 2) whether or not we should still have a global "I 
want to receive e-mails" checkbox, if we're giving users more fine-grained ways to customize 
their e-mail experience.)</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
